## Summary

Two changes:

1. **`pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go`**: Added `validateDeploymentManifest` (checks for the `"cert-manager-istio-csr"` container) and wired it into `getDeploymentObject` right after decoding the bindata manifest and before any mutations. This mirrors the trustmanager pattern — if the bindata ever loses the expected container name, the operator returns an irrecoverable error instead of silently applying a broken deployment.

2. **`pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments_test.go`**: Added a table-driven `TestValidateDeploymentManifest` with three cases: valid manifest (from bindata), missing container (wrong name), and empty containers list. Both broken-manifest cases confirm the guard returns the expected error string.
